               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18470614-name-1073" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18470614-name-1073" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470614-name-1073" type="surname" value="CHEESEMAN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470614-name-1073" type="given" value="WILLIAM HENRY"></interp>WILLIAM HENRY CHEESEMAN</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Greenwich-market. On Sunday, the 16th of May, I went to a water-closet—I hung my watch on a nail, went away, and forgot it—I went there in half-an-hour—my watch was gone—I received information, and went to look after the prisoner—he said he did not steal the watch—he said, taking a penny spoon would be stealing, but taking the watch from the water-closet was not stealing—my watch was found on him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> Mr. <hi rend="smallCaps">O'BRIEN</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Where was the water-closet? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Adjoining the house—it was not locked—it had been used by the public.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18470614-name-1074" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18470614-name-1074" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
